subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
MALE. Clypeus deeply concave (
Fig. 5C
); scape ventrally with two parallel carinae; F1 weakly compressed, not wider than F2. Pronotum and propodeum dorsally with dense pale setae obscuring cuticular sculpture (
Fig. 1C
). Metacoxa flattened with dense erect pale microsetae (
Fig. 7C
). T7 with narrow elongate impunctate line forming weak tubercle posteriorly; cuspis narrowed posteriorly in inner view (
Fig. 10C
). FEMALE. T2 pale setal spots large, densely setose, well defined (
Fig. 2B
); distance between T2 spots 0.3–0.5 × spot diameter; pale setal bands on T3–4 medially widely interrupted by black setae (
Fig. 2B
); pygidial plate coarsely irregularly rugose on anterior half, smooth posteriorly (
Fig. 12B
).

